.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E69FFE5FF3F7607DBD5F97D" blockId="27.[192,1441,1325,1670]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FF3F7607DE4CFABE" bold="true" box="[192,338,1325,1349]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Definition.</emphasis>
A genus in the same clade with 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E69FFE5FD097607DB48FABD" authority="Hayward, 1938" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1938" box="[758,1110,1325,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Neoxeniades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FD097607DC90FABE" box="[758,910,1325,1349]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Neoxeniades</emphasis>
Hayward, 1938
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E69FFE5FB977604DB80FABD" box="[1128,1182,1326,1350]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E69FFE5FAF77607DD1EFA9D" authority="Hayward, 1938" authorityName="Hayward" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Neoxeniades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="musarion">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FAF77607DE2BFA9E" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Neoxeniades musarion</emphasis>
Hayward, 1938
</taxonomicName>
) and far removed from 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E69FFE5FCCB7667DB64FA9D" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[820,1146,1357,1382]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Rhinthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FCCB7667DCB6FA9E" box="[820,936,1357,1381]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Rhinthon</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E69FFE5FB727664DBDDFA9D" box="[1165,1219,1358,1382]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E69FFE5FAD07667DD1EFA7D" authority="Mabille, 1889" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Proteides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiriquensis">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FAD07667DE4BFA7E" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Proteides chiriquensis</emphasis>
Mabille, 1889
</taxonomicName>
treated as a junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E69FFE5FC057644DA30FA7D" authority="Plotz, 1882" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1882" box="[1018,1326,1390,1414]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="osca">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FC057644DBBFFA7E" box="[1018,1185,1390,1413]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Hesperia osca</emphasis>
Pl√∂tz, 1882
</taxonomicName>
) where it was previously placed, but does not belong (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E69FFE5FD2876A4DC32FA5D" box="[727,812,1422,1446]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="25.[192,275,1594,1616]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,215,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[192,1440,213,1561]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 10. Genomic trees of Erionotini, Carystina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677255/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) in agreement with Burns et al. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E69FFE5FB3B76A4DA86FA5D" author="Burns" box="[1220,1432,1422,1446]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Burns" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" pagination="69 - 78" refId="ref26794" refString="Burns, J. M., D. H. Janzen, W. Hallwachs, M. Hajibabaei, and P. D. N. Hebert. 2010. Genitalia, DNA barcodes, larval facies, and foodplants place the mimetic species Neoxeniades molion in Rhinthon (Hesperiidae: Hesperiinae). Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society 64 (2): 69 - 78." type="journal article" year="2010">Burns et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
) and Smith et al. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E69FFE5FE6C7684DD79FA3D" author="Smith" box="[403,615,1454,1478]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" refId="ref28311" refString="Smith, D. S., L. D. Miller, and J. Y. Miller. 1994. The butterflies of the West Indies and South Florida. Oxford Univ. Press; Oxford, New York, Tokyo. x + 264 p." type="book" year="1994">Smith et al. 1994</bibRefCitation>
), who also questioned its position in 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E69FFE5FBDA7687DB87FA3E" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[1061,1177,1453,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Rhinthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FBDA7687DB87FA3E" box="[1061,1177,1453,1477]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Rhinthon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but did not propose a proper genus for it. Keys to L. 
<quantity id="4CDF35D17E69FFE5FDD376E4DD6DFA1D" box="[556,627,1486,1510]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0827999999999998" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="8.2">8.2 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E69FFE5FD8676E4DC00FA1D" author="Evans" box="[633,798,1486,1510]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E69FFE5FB7476E4DA01FA1D" box="[1163,1311,1486,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hesperiidae</taxonomicName>
by unique pattern in the basal half of brown ventral hindwing consisting of five spots: three connected, silvery-white, the one in the distal half of discal cell framed yellow, and two others towards tornus, and two small yellow ones, near the base of the cell and past it; and orange fringes in tornal area of both wings, dark brown elsewhere. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly2487.23.1:C242G, aly13410.9.1:G2107T, aly2700.17.1:G706A, aly 
<date id="FF99BEF47E69FFE5FD037544DC78F97D" box="[764,870,1646,1670]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" value="1407-07-06">1407.7.6</date>
:A2449C, aly 
<date id="FF99BEF47E69FFE5FBFF7544DB77F97D" box="[1024,1129,1646,1670]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" value="1283-09-01">1283.9.1</date>
:A694G.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E69FFE5FF3F75B4DC02F8CD" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E69FFE5FF3F75B4DB64F92D" blockId="27.[192,1440,1694,1750]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FF3F75B4DE45F94D" bold="true" box="[192,347,1694,1718]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular meant to suggest the incredibly unique looks of this awesome skipper with icy patches on the hindwing below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E69FFE5FF3F75C7DDDDF8FD" blockId="27.[192,707,1773,1798]" box="[192,707,1773,1798]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FF3F75C7DEAEF8FE" bold="true" box="[192,432,1773,1797]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Species included.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E69FFE5FDD675C4DD40F8FD" box="[553,606,1774,1798]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E69FFE5FF3F7434DC02F8CD" blockId="27.[192,796,1822,1846]" box="[192,796,1822,1846]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="B95344267E69FFE5FF3F7434DE62F8CD" bold="true" box="[192,380,1822,1846]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E69FFE5FE0A7434DC07F8CD" authority="Mabille 1878" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1878" box="[501,793,1822,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carystina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Carystina Mabille 1878</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
